Name: X-linked chondrodysplasia punctata 1
Definition: A chondrodysplasia punctata that is characterized by maxillary hypoplasia

Name: autosomal dominant chondrodysplasia punctata
Definition: A chondrodysplasia punctata that is characterized by abnormal facies and stippling of the limbs

Name: X-linked chondrodysplasia punctata 2
Definition: A chondrodysplasia puncata that has_material_basis_in mutation in the gene encoding delta(8)-delta(7) sterol isomerase emopamil-binding protein on chromosome Xp11.

Name: rhizomelic chondrodysplasia punctata
Definition: A chondrodysplasia punctata that is characterized by disproportionately short stature primarily affecting the proximal parts of the extremities
